Get started by creating an htpasswd file before starting the container. 

htpasswd -c ./htpasswd jamal
htpasswd ./htpasswd alice
htpasswd ./htpasswd bob


Renew the SSL certificate:
1 - Stop the standard container
2 - Start the certbot container
  $ docker compose -f compose.certbot.yaml up -d
3 - Run certbot command to renew the certificate
  $ certbot certonly --webroot --webroot-path ~/repos/dockerized-desktops/browser-shell/nginx/certbot-html -d <fully-qualified-domain-name>